UNITED STATES, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. William F. DOYLE, Defendant-Appellant. No. 251. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 4, 1931. Ilo Orleans, Alfred J. Talley, and Samuel Ealk, all of New York City, for appellant. George Z. Medalie, U. S. Atty., of New York City (John A. Wilson, Edward I. Aran-ow, and Seymour Altmark, Asst. U. S. Attys., all of New York City, of counsel), for the United States.

Before MANTON, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order, 42 F.(2d) 686, reversed in open court.
